<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-525-750  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 525 750.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Programming Languages andamp; Systems  April 1990v12 n2 p253(50).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A method for specializing logic programs. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bossi, A.; Cocco, N.; Dulli, S.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Users are demanding software with guaranteed reliability.andO;Frequently, though, the design of a program that meetsspecifications as closely as possible does not produce anefficient program.andP;  The transformation method permits theprogrammer to focus on the aspect of correctness of programs anddelay considerations about efficiency until a later stage.andP;  Thisallows the inefficient program to be transformed into moreefficient versions.andP;  Program specialization makes use oftransformation techniques to restrict the domain of a generalprogram so that a particular and restricted program can beobtained.andP;  This results in a collection of guaranteed correct,special-purpose, efficient programs from a single, verified,general program.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Program Development TechniquesSoftware EngineeringSoftware ValidationProgram Verification.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>